"attrs":{
"rowSpan":"1",
"colSpan":"1"
},
"children":[
" ",
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"78d0bf",
"class":"cell txt li",
"children":[
"Typical microorganisms consistent with infective endocarditis from two separate blood cultures: Viridans streptococci, ",
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"i",
"attrs":{
},
"children":[
"Streptococcus bovis"
]
},
", HACEK group (",
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"i",
"attrs":{
},
"children":[
"Haemophilus"
]
},
" spp., ",
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"i",
"attrs":{
},
"children":[
"Actinobacillus actinomycetemcomitans"
]
},
", ",
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"i",
"attrs":{
},
"children":[
"Cardiobacterium hominis"
]
},
", ",
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"i",
"attrs":{
},
"children":[
"Eikenella"
]
},
" spp., and ",
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"i",
"attrs":{
},
"children":[
"Kingella kingae"
]
},
"), ",
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"i",
"attrs":{
},
"children":[
"Staphylococcus aureus"
]
},
"; or community-acquired enterococci, in the absence of a primary focus; or"
]
},
" "
]
}
]
},
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"tr",
"attrs":{
"className":"group_1-1 row-odd"
},
"children":[
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"td",
"attrs":{
"rowSpan":"1",
"colSpan":"1"
},
"children":[
" ",
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"b8afc4",
"class":"cell txt li",
"children":[
"Microorganisms consistent with infective endocarditis from persistently positive blood cultures, defined as follows:"
]
},
" "
]
}
]
},
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"tr",
"attrs":{
"className":"group_1-1 row-odd"
},
"children":[
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"td",
"attrs":{
"rowSpan":"1",
"colSpan":"1"
},
"children":[
" ",
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"6b90b6",
"class":"cell txt lii",
"children":[
"At least two positive cultures of blood samples drawn 12 h apart; or"
]
},
" "
]
}
]
},
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"tr",
"attrs":{
"className":"group_1-1 row-odd"
},
"children":[
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"td",
"attrs":{
"rowSpan":"1",
"colSpan":"1"
},
"children":[
" ",
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"5a9870",
"class":"cell txt lii",
"children":[
"All of three or a majority of at least four separate cultures of blood (with first and last samples drawn at least 1 h apart)"
]
},
" "
]
}
]
},
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"tr",
"attrs":{
"className":"group_1-1 row-odd"
},
"children":[
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"td",
"attrs":{
"rowSpan":"1",
"colSpan":"1"
},
"children":[
" ",
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"75d246",
"class":"cell txt li",
"children":[
"Single blood culture positive for ",
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"i",
"attrs":{
},
"children":[
"Coxiella burnetii"
]
},
" or antiphase I IgG antibody titer >1:800"
]
},
" "
]
}
]
},
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"tr",
"attrs":{
"className":"group_1-2 row-even"
},
"children":[
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"td",
"attrs":{
"rowSpan":"1",
"colSpan":"1"
},
"children":[
" ",
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"75b499",
"class":"cell txt l",
"children":[
"Evidence of endocardial involvement"
]
},
" "
]
}
]
},
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"tr",
"attrs":{
"className":"group_1-2 row-even"
},
"children":[
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"td",
"attrs":{
"rowSpan":"1",
"colSpan":"1"
},
"children":[
" ",
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"bad84c",
"class":"cell txt li",
"children":[
"Echocardiogram positive for infective endocarditis (TEE recommended in patients with prosthetic valves, rated at least “possible infective endocarditis” by clinical criteria, or complicated infective endocarditis [paravalvular abscess]; TTE as first test in other patients), defined as follows:"
]
},
" "
]
}
]
},
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"tr",
"attrs":{
"className":"group_1-2 row-even"
},
"children":[
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"td",
"attrs":{
"rowSpan":"1",
"colSpan":"1"
},
"children":[
" ",
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"1483c0",
"class":"cell txt lii",
"children":[
"Oscillating intracardiac mass on valve or supporting structures, in the path of regurgitant jets, or on implanted material in the absence of an alternative anatomic explanation; or"
]
},
" "
]
}
]
},
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"tr",
"attrs":{
"className":"group_1-2 row-even"
},
"children":[
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"td",
"attrs":{
"rowSpan":"1",
"colSpan":"1"
},
"children":[
" ",
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"e3a388",
"class":"cell txt lii",
"children":[
"Abscess; or"
]
},
" "
]
}
]
},
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"tr",
"attrs":{
"className":"group_1-2 row-even"
},
"children":[
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"td",
"attrs":{
"rowSpan":"1",
"colSpan":"1"
},
"children":[
" ",
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"50fe81",
"class":"cell txt lii",
"children":[
"New partial dehiscence of prosthetic valve"
]
},
" "
]
}
]
},
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"tr",
"attrs":{
"className":"group_1-2 row-even"
},
"children":[
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"td",
"attrs":{
"rowSpan":"1",
"colSpan":"1"
},
"children":[
" ",
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"f7e36a",
"class":"cell txt li",
"children":[
"New valvular regurgitation (worsening or changing of pre-existing murmur not sufficient)"
]
},
" "
]
}
]
},
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"tr",
"attrs":{
},
"children":[
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"th",
"attrs":{
"rowSpan":"1",
"colSpan":"1"
},
"children":[
" ",
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"8a5855",
"class":"col hd l",
"children":[
